1. *Dječak* je trčao kroz park. (The boy ran through the park.)
2. Vidio sam *dječaka* kako igra fudbal. (I saw the boy playing football.)
3. *Dječaci* vole igrati videoigrice. (Boys like to play video games.)
4. Naš *dječak* je dobio nagradu za najboljeg učenika. (Our boy got an award for being the best student.)
5. *Dječak* je bio nasmijan i sretan kada je dobio poklon. (The boy was smiling and happy when he received a gift.)
6. Volim kad *dječaci* pjevaju u školskom zboru. (I love it when boys sing in the school choir.)
7. *Dječaku* je bilo hladno pa mu je majka dala jaknu. (The boy was cold, so his mother gave him a jacket.)
8. *Dječaci* su se igrali nogometa na livadi. (The boys were playing football in the meadow.)
9. *Dječak* je gledao u daljinu dok je razmišljao o svom snu. (The boy was looking into the distance while thinking about his dream.)
10. Naučio sam *dječaka* kako se vozi bicikl. (I taught the boy how to ride a bike.)

Note: In Serbian, "dječak" means "boy". The word has different forms depending on its grammatical function in the sentence. In these examples, we used the nominative, accusative, plural, genitive, dative, and instrumental cases.